p10
aVPerhaps you've even said them.
p11
aVAnd if so, you wouldn't be alone, and you wouldn't be entirely wrong.
p12
aVThe game of public policy today is rigged in many ways.
p13
aVHow else would more than half of federal tax breaks
p14
aVflow up to the wealthiest five percent of Americans?
p15
aVAnd our choices indeed are often terrible.
p16
aVFor many people across the political spectrum,
p17
aVExhibit A is the 2016 presidential election.
p18
aVBut in any year, you can look up and down the ballot
p19
aVand find plenty to be uninspired about.
