aa(lp191
VBecause remember, all citizenship is local.
p192
aVWhen politics becomes just a presidential election,
p193
aVwe yell and we scream at our screens, and then we collapse, exhausted.
p194
aVBut when politics is about us
p195
aVand our neighbors and other people in our community
p196
aVcoming together to create experiences of collective voice and imagination,
p197
aVthen we begin to remember that this stuff matters.
p198
aVWe begin to remember that this is the stuff of self-government.
